GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 988
Short Title: Revise Law on Instant Bingo. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Hawkins.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REVISE THE LAWS GOVERNING INSTANT BINGO GAMES, TO REVISE
3 THE METHOD BY WHICH FUNDS RECEIVED IN CONNECTION WITH A BINGO
4 GAME MAY BE DISBURSED, AND TO MAKE VARIOUS TECHNICAL
5 CORRECTIONS.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. G.S. 14-309.6 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 14-309.6. Definitions.
9 For purposes of this Part, the term:following definitions apply:
10 (1) "Exempt organization" means anExempt organization. – An organization that
11 has been in continuous existence in the county of operation of the bingo game
12 for at least one year and that is exempt from taxation under section 501(c)(3),
13 501(c)(4), 501(c)(8), 501(c)(10), 501(c)(19), or 501(d) of the Internal
14 Revenue Code and is exempt under similar provisions of the General Statutes
15 as a bona fide nonprofit charitable, civic, religious, fraternal, patriotic or
16 veterans' organization or as a nonprofit volunteer fire department, or as a
17 nonprofit volunteer rescue squad or a bona fide homeowners' or property
18 owners' association. (If the organization has local branches or chapters, the
19 term "exempt organization" means the local branch or chapter operating the
20 bingo game);game).
21 (2) "Bingo game" means aBingo game. – A specific game of chance played with
22 individual cards having numbered squares ranging from one to 75, in which
23 prizes are awarded on the basis of designated numbers on such cards
24 conforming to a predetermined pattern of numbers (but shall not include
25 "instant bingo" which is a game of chance played by the selection of one or
26 more prepackaged cards, with winners determined by the appearance of a
27 preselected designation on the card);numbers. This term includes instant
28 bingo.
29 (2a) Instant bingo. – A game of chance played by the selection of one or more
30 predesignated paper or digital tickets, with winners determined by the
31 appearance of a preselected designation on the ticket.
32 …
33 (4) "Local law-enforcement agency" means forLocal law enforcement agency. –
34 For any bingo game conducted outside the corporate limits of a municipality
