18 of that organization."
19 SECTION 2. G.S. 14-309.8 reads as rewritten:
20 "§ 14-309.8. Limit on sessions.
21 The number of sessions of bingo conducted or sponsored by an exempt organization shall be
22 limited to two sessions per week and such sessions must not exceed a period of five hours each
23 per session. No two sessions of bingo shall be held within a 48-hour period of time. No more
24 than two sessions of bingo shall be operated or conducted in any one building, hall or structure
25 during any one calendar week and if two sessions are held, they must be held by the same exempt
26 organization. This section shall not apply to bingo games conducted (i) at a fair or other
27 exhibition conducted pursuant to Article 45 of Chapter 106 of the General Statutes.Statutes or
28 (ii) by an organization exempt from taxation under section 501(c)(8), 501(c)(10), or 501(c)(19)
29 of the Internal Revenue Code."
30 SECTION 3. G.S. 14-309.9(a) reads as rewritten:
31 "(a) TheExcept as otherwise provided in this section, the maximum prize in cash or
32 merchandise that may be offered or paid for any one game of bingo is five hundred dollars
33 ($500.00). The maximum aggregate amount of prizes, in cash and/orcash, merchandise, or cash
34 and merchandise, that may be offered or paid at any one session of bingo is one thousand five
35 hundred dollars ($1,500). Provided, however, that if an exempt organization holds only one
36 session of bingo during a calendar week, the maximum aggregate amount of prizes, in cash
37 and/orcash, merchandise, or cash and merchandise, that may be offered or paid at any one session
38 is two thousand five hundred dollars ($2,500). The maximum prize in cash or merchandise that
39 may be offered or paid for any one game of instant bingo is six hundred dollars ($600.00)."
40 SECTION 4. G.S. 14-309.10 reads as rewritten:
41 "§ 14-309.10. Operation of bingo.
42 (a) The operation of bingo games shall be the direct responsibility of, and controlled by,
43 a special committee selected by the governing body of the exempt organization in the manner
44 provided by the rules of the exempt organization.
45 (b) Only organizations exempt from taxation under section 501(c)(8), 501(c)(10), or
46 501(c)(19) of the Internal Revenue Code may conduct instant bingo.
47 (c) Paper instant bingo tickets shall comply with the standards for instant bingo tickets
48 or cards established by the North American Gaming Regulators Association, as amended from
49 time to time.
