1 (d) Prior to use, electronic instant bingo systems shall be tested by an independent gaming
2 test laboratory and certified as compliant with the GLI-14 standard produced by Gaming
3 Laboratories International, LLC."
4 SECTION 5. G.S. 14-309.11 reads as rewritten:
5 "§ 14-309.11. Accounting and use of proceeds.
6 (a) All funds received in connection with a bingo game shall be placed in a separate bank
7 account. No funds may be disbursed from this account except the exempt organization may
8 expend proceeds for prizes, advertising, utilities, and the purchase of supplies and equipment
9 used in conducting the raffle and in playing bingo, taxes and license fees related to bingo
10 andbingo, the payment of compensation as authorized by G.S. 14-309.7(c)14-309.7(c), and for
11 the purposes set forth below for the remaining proceeds. Such payments shall be made by
12 consecutively numbered checks.checks or by electronic funds transfer. Any proceeds available
13 in the account after payment of the above expenses shall inure to the exempt organization to be
14 used for religious, charitable, civic, scientific, testing, public safety, literary, or educational
15 purposes or for purchasing, constructing, maintaining, operating or using equipment or land or a
16 building or improvements thereto owned by and for the exempt organization and used for civic
17 purposes or made available by the exempt organization for use by the general public from time
18 to time, or to foster amateur sports competition, or for the prevention of cruelty to children or
19 animals, provided that no proceeds shall be used or expended for social functions for the members
20 of the exempt organization.
21 (b) An audit of the account required by subsection (a) of this section shall be prepared
22 annually for the period of January 1 through December 31 or otherwise as directed by the Alcohol
23 Law Enforcement Division of the Department of Public Safety and shall be filed with the
24 Division and the local law-enforcement agency at a time directed by the Division. The audit shall
25 be prepared on a form approved by the Division and shall include all of the following
26 information:
27 (1) The number of bingo games conducted or sponsored by the exempt
28 organization;organization.
29 (2) The location and date at which each bingo game was conducted and the prize
30 awarded;awarded.
31 (3) The gross receipts of each bingo game;game.
32 (4) The cost or amount of any prize given at each bingo game;game.
33 (5) The amount paid in prizes at each session;session.
34 (6) The net return to the exempt organization; andorganization.
35 (7) The disbursements from the separate account and the purpose of those
36 disbursements, including the date of each transaction and the name and
37 address of each payee.
38 …."
39 SECTION 6. This act becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to bingo
40 games conducted on or after that date.
